metadata.name: Sengen せん
metadata.description:
The Goddess of Fuji is also protector of sakura's.

Owner of unparalleled beauty, Sengen accumulates vast symbolism, which includes health and compassion.

At the top of Mount Fuji or Fuji-no-Yama (the mountain of Fuji) is located the temple Sengen-sama, where the Goddess of Fuji is worshipped. It is said that in ancient times this Goddess hovered in a luminous cloud above the crater, attended by servants invisible to mortal eyes, ready to hurl any pilgrim who did not have a pure heart into her depths.

In Japanese mythology, Konohana Sakuya Hime, or just Sakuya Hime, is the daughter of the mountain god Ohoyamatsumi and granddaughter of the famous Goddess Amaterasu, daughter of Izanagi and Izanami, creator gods of the Japanese archipelago.

The Goddess Sakuya Hime accumulates vast symbolism in her mythology, which included health, longevity and compassion. The Goddess also represents ephemeral love
